headline: 1 Healthcare Stock with Solid Fundamentals and 2 to Turn Down
summary: From novel pharmaceuticals to telemedicine, most healthcare companies are on a mission to drive better patient outcomes. But financial performance has lagged recently as players offloaded surplus COVID inventories in 2023 and 2024, a headwind for overall demand. The result? Over the past six months, the industry has tumbled by 9.2%. This performance was worse than the S&P 500’s 1.8% loss.
